   <b>(2) Clause:</b> ISO/TS 10303-1060 :2004(E) Product concept identification
 </p>
 <p>
   <b>(3) Paragraph:</b> 4.1.2 Product_concept
 </p>
 <p>
   <b>(5) Comment:</b>
 </p>
 <p>
A Product_concept represents a conceptual idea of a class of similar products that are offered to a Market. There might be several levels of product_concept(s) defined in a company. The description of product concept structures and relationships is not supported by the current PLCS Schema.
</p>
 <p>
   <b>(6) Proposal:</b>
 </p>
 <p>
Consider making product_concept a subtype of view_definition_context.
</p>
